The human toll of the conflict can be measured by the death and displacement of thousands.To save Ethiopia, the US, EU and Africa should use their diplomatic muscles to negotiate a ceasefire in the Tigray conflict. Ethiopia is sliding into a man-made disaster. The tension between the Tigray People’s Liberation Front (TPLF), a group that had misruled Ethiopia for three decades and the federal government has been mounting for months.
It exploded into a full scale conflict on November 4 when Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed launched a military retaliation after the TPLF staged an attack against Ethiopian Defence Forces bases in the Tigray region, massacring the members of the army.



