Finally, keeping a blind eye on the human suffering of the Tigray conflict would only foment combustible ethnic or religious driven violence, shattering Ethiopia’s peace and stability, and sending waves of refugees into a region already plagued by wars.  Residents of Mombasa have been eagerly waiting the commissioning of the bridge. Ms Nthenya was freed without any charges being preferred against her. Just last week, Justice James Rika recused himself from the case after tempers flared in court.